Description: Backport procfs private-data and proc_ops compatibility
 Modern kernels removed the old PDE(inode)->data fallback and switched
 proc_create_data() to receive struct proc_ops instead of struct
 file_operations. Add explicit conftests for lowercase pde_data(),
 uppercase PDE_DATA(), the direct legacy proc_dir_entry member fallback,
 and proc_ops support, then centralize operation-table field selection in
 nv-procfs.h.
Origin: backport, NVIDIA legacy procfs compatibility design adapted for 367.134
Forwarded: not-needed
